css selectors (Cascading Style Sheet)
it is a way of locating elelments on the web page

Syntax:
tagname[attribute = 'attribute value']
input[value = 'LOGIN']
CSS DOSE NOT GIVE US AN OPPORTUNITY TO LOCATE THE ELELMENT BY ITS TEXT

SHORTCUTS OF CSS:
Shortcut for the className is (.)
Syntax: tagname.classNameValue
e.g.    input.button
Shortcut for ID is (#)
Syntex: tagname#id
e.g.   input#txtPassword

contains()   method in CSS:
(*) will represent contains() method
S:  tagname[attribute *='partial attribute value']
e.g.  input[placeholder*='phone']


 starts-with method in CSS:
 (^) is a circumflex symbol represent stars with method
 tagname[attribute^='startikng attribute value']
 e.g.  input[aria-label^='Pas']


 ends-with methods in CSS:
( $ ) is symbol that represent ends-with method in SCC
 tagname [attribute$='ending attribute value']
 e.g.     a[href$='login']

 Xpath vs CSS:
 + CSS cannot locate the elements by text whereas xpath can
 + css has shortcuts
 + XPATH does not have ends-with method
 + CSS has more simple syntax than xpath

states of an elements:
enable
displayed
selected

WebElement Command:
consists of several method where we can perform an action and
get the element state on the webpage

 isEnabled()--> boolean
 isDisplaed()-->boolean
 isSelected()--boolean
 clear()-- void
 getText()--String
 getAttribute()-->String
 submit()-->void

<a>  is an attribute in HTML code whrere link are stored



